Variant(T) - Constructor for class Variant
Creates a Variant that represents a specific AllJoyn data type and value.
Variant(T, String) - Constructor for class Variant
Creates a Variant with an explicit signature that represents a specific AllJoyn data type and instance value.
VariantTypeReference<T> - Class in org.alljoyn.bus
Used when calling Variant.getObject(Class) where the wrapped object is a generic type such as Map<K, V>.
VariantTypeReference() - Constructor for class VariantTypeReference
 
violated(Status) - Method in interface SecurityViolationListener
Called when an attempt to decrypt an encrypted messages failed or when an unencrypted message was received on an interface that requires encryption.
